data.name: DrdaArActiveDrdaSessionsHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the number of currently active DRDA sessions.

data.name: DrdaArAverageHostProcessingTimeHelp
data.value: This average time counter measures the time the host takes to respond to a request sent to it. The time starts after MSDRDA sends the final data buffer and ends when the first response buffer is received by MSDRDA. This counter is represented in terms of seconds of elapsed time.

data.name: DrdaArBytesReceivedPerSecondHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the number of bytes received by the client. This number is represented in terms of bytes per second.

data.name: DrdaArBytesSentPerSecondHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the number of bytes sent from the client. This number is represented in terms of bytes per second.

data.name: DrdaArOpenStatementsHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the total number of currently active statements created by data providers for DRDA.

data.name: DrdaArTotalTransactionsHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the total number of transactions. Transactions equals the number of commits plus the number of rollbacks.

data.name: DrdaArTransactionCommitsPerSecondHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the rate of transaction processing which result in a commit. This number is represented in terms of commits per second.

data.name: DrdaArTransactionRollbacksPerSecondHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the rate of transaction processing which result in a rollback. This number is represented in terms of rollbacks per second.

data.name: DrdaArTransactionsPerSecondHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the rate of transaction processing. Transactions equals the number of commits plus the number of rollbacks. This number is represented in terms of transactions per second.

data.name: DrdaAsActiveSqlConnectionsHelp

data.name: DrdaAsActiveTransactionsHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the number of currently active transactions.

data.name: DrdaAsBytesReceivedPerSecondHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the number of bytes received from a client. This number is represented in terms of bytes per second.

data.name: DrdaAsBytesSentPerSecondHelp

data.name: HipAverageHostResponseTimeHelp
data.value: This counter measures the average time it takes for a response to arrive from the host system. The time begins when TI sends the request to the host system and ends when TI receives the first packet of the host response.

data.name: HipAverageMethodCallTimeHelp
data.value: This counter measures the average time it takes TI HIP to process method calls made by the client application. The time begins when TI receives the request from the client application and ends when TI returns control to the client application.

data.name: HipCumulativeCallsHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the total number of method calls that have occurred since the TI Application was started.

data.name: HipCurrentlyExecutingCallsHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the number of method calls that are currently in the process of being executed.

data.name: HipTotalCallsPerSecondHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the total number of method calls that TI HIP has processed. This counter is not specific to any TI HIP programming model. This number is represented in terms of calls per second.

data.name: HipTotalErrorsPerSecondHelp
data.value: This counter indicates the total number of method calls that have returned a non-zero HRESULT indication to the client application. This counter is not specific to any TI HIP programming model. This number is represented in terms of errors per second.

data.name: MqClientAverageGetTimeHelp
data.value: This counter measures the average time it takes the Microsoft Client for MQ to process GET calls made by the client application. The time begins when the Microsoft Client for MQ receives the request from the client application and ends when it returns control to the client application.

data.name: MqClientAveragePutTimeHelp

data.name: MqClientAverageTransactionalGetTimeHelp
